Removal + root dev orchestration (dev:all) + env-check hardening

Reply 1 atau 2.

mungkin kita boleh suruh codex review file yang ada atau tool yang ada di mobile yang belum ada di brand-os?

Ya ‚Äî itu pendekatan yang tepat dari sudut capability harvesting sebelum kita ‚Äúsunset‚Äù abang-colek-mobile. Kita treat mobile sebagai feature donor: kita audit toolchain + integrations yang mungkin bernilai, kemudian kita port yang relevan ke abang-colek-brand-os (atau ke wocs-server) dan barulah kita delete.

Di bawah ialah Codex playbook untuk buat review yang ‚Äúno-regrets‚Äù.

1) Codex Prompt: Capability & Tool Gap Analysis (Mobile ‚Üí Brand-OS)

Paste dalam Codex:

Use the sequentialthinking tool.

Objective: Perform a capability harvest from abang-colek-mobile before it is removed.
Goal: Identify tools/features/integrations present in abang-colek-mobile that are NOT present in abang-colek-brand-os, and propose a migration plan.

Steps:
1) Inventory abang-colek-mobile:
   - package.json dependencies/devDependencies/scripts
   - config files (tsconfig, eslint, prettier, env usage, build tooling)
   - server folder (local API) capabilities, endpoints, auth, db, redis usage
   - integrations hinted by env vars (OAuth, WhatsApp, Forge APIs)
2) Inventory abang-colek-brand-os similarly.
3) Produce a GAP MATRIX:
   - Category: Auth, DB, Cache, WhatsApp, Payments, Analytics, Content ops, Admin tooling, Dev tooling
   - For each gap: what exists in mobile, what‚Äôs missing in brand-os, and whether it should be migrated.
4) Migration decision per gap:
   - Migrate to Brand-OS frontend
   - Migrate to WOCS server backend
   - Drop (not needed / duplicate / high risk)
5) Output:
   - GAP_MATRIX.md (paste-ready)
   - MIGRATION_PLAN.md (phases + file-level actions + risk/mitigation)
Constraints:
- Do not invent endpoints or features; confirm by reading actual files.
- Use repo search and targeted file reads.

2) Command Pack (untuk bagi Codex ‚Äúevidence‚Äù cepat)

Run ini di terminal (root repo):

# A) High signal inventory
ls abang-colek-mobile
ls abang-colek-brand-os

# B) Compare dependency surface
cat abang-colek-mobile/package.json
cat abang-colek-brand-os/package.json

# C) Locate ‚Äúcapabilities‚Äù by folders
find abang-colek-mobile -maxdepth 3 -type d
find abang-colek-brand-os -maxdepth 3 -type d

# D) Hunt env-driven integrations
cat abang-colek-mobile/.env 2>/dev/null || true
rg -n "process\.env|import\.meta\.env|DATABASE_URL|OAUTH|WHATSAPP|REDIS|FORGE|JWT|SUPABASE" abang-colek-mobile abang-colek-brand-os

# E) Identify backend-like modules in mobile
find abang-colek-mobile/server -maxdepth 4 -type f 2>/dev/null || true
rg -n "router|get\(|post\(|app\.use|express|hono|fastify|prisma|drizzle|knex|redis|bull|queue|webhook" abang-colek-mobile/server 2>/dev/null || true


Ini akan bagi Codex data yang cukup untuk buat gap matrix yang ‚Äúdefensible‚Äù.

3) Apa yang biasanya ‚Äúbernilai‚Äù untuk dipindahkan (heuristik)

Berdasarkan env vars yang anda share sebelum ini, mobile berpotensi ada:

OAuth server integration (OAUTH_SERVER_URL, OWNER_OPEN_ID)

JWT/auth middleware (JWT_SECRET)

Local API patterns (routes, validation, error handling)

DB access layer (DATABASE_URL) ‚Äî schema, ORM, migrations

WhatsApp token handling (verify token/access token) ‚Äî walaupun idealnya ini duduk di wocs-server, bukan frontend web

Keputusan prinsip:

Anything secret / token / DB ‚Üí move to wocs-server

Anything UI/admin ops ‚Üí move to abang-colek-brand-os

Anything dev tooling (lint, tsconfig, env-check) ‚Üí move to root repo standard

4) Jika mobile sudah terdelete: buat harvest dari Git history

Kalau anda dah buang folder tu, masih boleh harvest dari Git.

Codex prompt alternatif:

Use the sequentialthinking tool.

If abang-colek-mobile folder is missing, recover its content from git history to perform the same gap analysis.
- Identify last commit where abang-colek-mobile existed.
- Extract package.json + server/_core + key config files for review without permanently restoring the folder.
- Produce GAP_MATRIX.md and MIGRATION_PLAN.md as before.


Terminal helpers:

git log -- abang-colek-mobile | head
# pick a commit hash, then:
git show <HASH>:abang-colek-mobile/package.json
git ls-tree -r --name-only <HASH> | rg "abang-colek-mobile"

5) Fast alignment (so we don‚Äôt over-migrate)

Beritahu saya target outcome anda:

Anda nak Brand-OS jadi ‚ÄúAdmin Dashboard‚Äù yang control WOCS + content + analytics?

Atau nak Brand-OS kekal marketing/brand-only dan semua ops di backend?

Jika anda jawab satu ayat (contoh: ‚ÄúBrand-OS mesti jadi admin dashboard‚Äù), saya akan bagi migration filter yang jelas: apa yang wajib diambil dari mobile, apa yang wajib dibuang.

