*Proposal by: Antigravity AI*  
*Date: 17 January 2026*  
*Status: Pending Approval*
Thought for a couple of seconds

Baik. Dokumen proposal ini sudah cukup ‚Äúinvestment-ready‚Äù dari segi narrative dan flow. Sekarang kita buat operationalization: kita gunakan Codex untuk audit repo semasa (v1.0) dan buat gap-to-scope mapping supaya:

kita tahu apa yang sudah wujud dalam abang-colek-brand-os / wocs-server

apa yang masih ‚Äúpaper-only‚Äù dalam proposal v2.0

apa yang patut di-‚Äúharvest‚Äù dari abang-colek-mobile sebelum kita buang

Di bawah saya bagi Codex Prompt Pack yang terus menghasilkan artefak yang anda perlukan: GAP_MATRIX.md, BACKLOG.md, ARCH_UPDATE.md, dan MOBILE_HARVEST.md.

A) Codex Prompt: Audit Repo vs Proposal v2.0 (Gap Matrix + Backlog)

Paste dalam Codex:

Use the sequentialthinking tool.

Context:
We have a written proposal "ABANG COLEK KIOSK v2.0" describing 10 screens, lucky draw, payments, queue, WhatsApp notifications, and TikTok verification.
Repo is already cloned locally.

Objective:
Compare the current codebase capabilities (abang-colek-brand-os, wocs-server, abang-colek-wocs-extension, and abang-colek-mobile if still present) against the v2.0 proposal and produce an execution-ready gap analysis and backlog.

Tasks:
1) Identify where the current "kiosk v1.0 demo" lives in the repo:
   - locate voice ordering (Nina), function calling tools, CRT aesthetic, menu/order state, glitch/secret menu, animations
2) For each v2.0 module, determine status:
   - Already implemented (with file paths)
   - Partially implemented (with missing pieces)
   - Not implemented
Modules to map:
- 10 screens / routing
- Order model + cart
- Customer info capture (WhatsApp + TikTok)
- Payment: online + counter pay flows
- Queue management + staff panel + display
- Lucky Draw rule engine + LD-ID generator + state machine
- Selfie upload + storage
- TikTok URL submission + verification (manual workflow)
- Notifications (WhatsApp Cloud API)
- Realtime updates (Supabase realtime or server websockets)
- Admin dashboard

3) Output deliverables (paste-ready):
- GAP_MATRIX.md: rows = modules, columns = status, repo evidence (file paths), recommended owner (brand-os vs wocs-server vs supabase edge)
- BACKLOG.md: prioritized epics/stories with acceptance criteria and dependencies (Phase 1-5 aligned)
- ARCH_UPDATE.md: recommended target architecture (who owns what), including data ownership and security boundaries

Constraints:
- Do not invent features. Only mark as present if verified in code.
- Use targeted repository search and open files when needed.


Outcome: anda akan dapat backlog yang ‚Äúdelivery-grade‚Äù bukan sekadar idea.

B) Codex Prompt: Mobile ‚Üí Brand-OS ‚ÄúCapability Harvest‚Äù (sebelum delete)

Paste ini (buat ini dulu sebelum buang folder mobile):

Use the sequentialthinking tool.

Objective:
Harvest any valuable capabilities from abang-colek-mobile that should be migrated into the v2.0 Kiosk stack (brand-os / wocs-server) before abang-colek-mobile is removed.

Focus areas:
- Auth patterns (JWT, OAuth)
- API patterns (routing, validation, error handling)
- DB layer (schema, migrations, ORM)
- WhatsApp integration utilities
- Any queue/order primitives
- Any env/config discipline (lint/tsconfig, env loading)

Process:
1) Inventory abang-colek-mobile dependencies, scripts, and server folder capabilities.
2) Identify anything that directly accelerates v2.0: payment hooks, queue state, notification templates, storage upload, verification workflow.
3) Produce:
- MOBILE_HARVEST.md: "Keep / Migrate / Drop" table with exact file paths
- MIGRATION_PLAN.md: step-by-step porting plan with file-level actions
- DELETION_PLAN.md: safe removal checklist after harvest (workspace refs, docs, scripts)

Constraints:
- Do not migrate secrets or backend tokens to frontend. Any sensitive workflows must land in wocs-server or Supabase Edge.
- If a capability duplicates existing code in brand-os, recommend consolidation not duplication.

C) Architectural Call: ‚ÄúWho Owns What‚Äù (supabase vs wocs-server)

Untuk proposal v2.0, governance boundary ini penting supaya tak jadi tech-debt:

Recommended ownership model (clean separation)

Brand-OS (React PWA): UI/UX, screens, client state, Supabase client reads, ‚Äúkiosk flow‚Äù

Supabase (DB + Realtime + Storage): order data, queue_status, lucky_draw_entries, selfie storage, realtime subscriptions

Server-side secure layer (choose one):

Option 1 (lean): Supabase Edge Functions untuk payment webhook + WhatsApp send + verification endpoints

Option 2 (controlled): wocs-server sebagai integration hub (WhatsApp, Stripe webhook, rule engine) + optional Redis

Non-negotiable security principle:
Payment webhooks + WhatsApp token + verification logic jangan duduk dalam frontend.

Codex boleh buat recommendation berdasarkan apa yang sudah wujud dalam repo.

D) ‚ÄúExecutive Cut‚Äù MVP (supaya 5 minggu realistic)

Jika anda nak v2.0 cepat go-live, saya cadangkan MVP scope yang masih capai KPI viral loop:

Week 1‚Äì2 (MVP Go-Live)

Screens 1‚Äì7 sahaja (Splash ‚Üí Promo ‚Üí Order ‚Üí Cart ‚Üí Customer Info ‚Üí Payment Method ‚Üí Confirmation)

Payment: Counter pay dulu (online payment optional)

Queue: simple (status NEW/PREPARING/READY/COMPLETE)

Lucky Draw: generate LD-ID + QUALIFIED (activation later)

WhatsApp: send ‚Äúorder received‚Äù + ‚Äúorder ready‚Äù (2 template je)

Week 3‚Äì4 (Activation Layer)

Selfie upload + TikTok URL submission

Manual verification workflow (staff toggle ACTIVATED)

VVIP upsell prompts by Nina

Week 5 (Polish & Hardening)

Observability, retries, admin roles, training docs

Codex backlog (Prompt A) akan auto align ini dalam Phase 1‚Äì5.

E) Kalau anda nak saya ‚Äústandardize output format‚Äù untuk Codex

Saya boleh bagi ‚Äúrubric‚Äù supaya Codex output konsisten:

Semua epic mesti ada: Definition of Done, Acceptance Criteria, Dependencies, Owner (Brand-OS / Server / Supabase)

Jika anda setuju, saya bagi prompt tambahan untuk enforce rubric.

Next action (paling high-leverage)

Buat dua run ini dulu:

Prompt B (Mobile harvest)

Prompt A (Repo vs Proposal gap matrix)

Lepas Codex keluarkan MOBILE_HARVEST.md dan GAP_MATRIX.md, paste balik ringkasan top 10 gaps (atau terus paste files tu). Saya akan bantu anda buat P0 execution plan yang ‚Äúno-waste‚Äù dan siap dengan order-of-operations untuk developer velocity.

aku nak start develop baru ke senang?

Secara prinsip, ya‚Äîstart baru selalunya lebih senang untuk v2.0 jika codebase v1.0 anda sekarang tidak ‚Äúmodular‚Äù dan terlalu demo-centric (CRT gimmick + voice) tanpa data model, routing 10 screen, dan ops layer (queue/payment/lucky draw). Dari sudut delivery, pilihan paling ‚Äúhigh-leverage‚Äù ialah:

Keputusan Strategik: Rebuild vs Refactor
Option A ‚Äî Rebuild (recommended untuk v2.0)

Bila ini menang:

v1.0 banyak hardcode, state bercampur, tiada domain model Order/Queue/LuckyDraw

UI/animation terlalu tight-coupled dengan logic

Anda nak ‚Äú10 screens + admin ops‚Äù yang clean dan scalable

Apa anda carry-over (assets yang tak patut burn):

CRT theme + components yang reusable

Nina voice tooling/function-calling contracts

Animations/glitch mode sebagai ‚Äúskin‚Äù layer sahaja

Risiko: anda kena set architecture betul dari awal (tapi itu sebenarnya kelebihan).

Option B ‚Äî Refactor (hanya kalau v1.0 sudah kemas)

Bila ini menang:

v1.0 dah ada routing, folder structure baik, state management ok

Nina integration clean (service layer), UI layer separated

Ada data persistence / backend integration already

Risiko: refactor boleh jadi ‚Äúinfinite cleanup‚Äù dan timeline 5 minggu boleh tergelincir.

Cadangan Saya (execution-first)

Start baru, tetapi dalam repo yang sama (monorepo), supaya:

Anda tak hilang sejarah dan asset

Anda boleh ‚Äúport‚Äù CRT + Nina layer dengan controlled migration

Anda boleh jalankan v1 dan v2 side-by-side sebagai fallback

Modelnya: Greenfield inside monorepo.

Struktur yang saya recommend

abang-colek-kiosk-v2/ (baru, production-grade)

abang-colek-brand-os/ (kekal untuk brand/admin‚Äîatau merge kemudian)

wocs-server/ (integration hub)

Minimum Viable Architecture untuk v2.0 (supaya tak serabut)

Frontend (React PWA): 10 screens + staff panel UI
Supabase: tables + realtime + storage selfie
Server-side secure: pilih satu:

Supabase Edge Functions (lean), atau

wocs-server (lebih control, sesuai WhatsApp Cloud API + Stripe webhook)

Untuk speed + kurang maintenance, saya condong Supabase Edge Functions untuk webhook/payment/whatsapp, dan wocs-server hanya kalau anda memang dah ada ops stack di sana.

