- LandingPage.tsx (or equivalent)
- Any small UI components created
- Update router entry to include "/"
- Provide a short checklist to verify locally
Constraints:
- No external assets required.
- Keep code clean and typed.

Optional (high ROI)

Add a mode auto-detect on landing:

If URL has ?mode=kiosk ‚Üí auto redirect /k/display

If ?mode=customer ‚Üí /c/splash

This makes QR posters flexible without creating many links.

If you want, I can give you the Codex prompt for that redirect logic + a QR strategy (poster QR vs booth QR vs staff QR) so funnel tracking is cleaner.

dan apps nie aku nak bagi semua peniaga boleh guna

Baik. Bila anda kata ‚Äúsemua peniaga boleh guna‚Äù, anda sedang pivot daripada single-brand app kepada multi-tenant SaaS (platform). Itu bermaksud kita perlu ubah design dari ‚ÄúAbang Colek only‚Äù kepada merchant-ready operating system‚Äîtanpa hilangkan ‚Äúbrand skin‚Äù Abang Colek.

Di bawah ialah blueprint yang paling ‚Äúscalable‚Äù untuk capai itu.

1) Product Strategy: One Platform, Many Merchants
A. Core platform (shared)

POS / Order / Queue

Customer capture (WhatsApp, TikTok optional)

Payments (online + counter)

Staff panel + admin ops

Analytics & reporting

Templates for campaigns (Lucky Draw / promo / membership)

B. Brand layer (per-merchant ‚Äúskin‚Äù)

Theme tokens (colors, fonts, CRT on/off)

Logo, tagline, assets

Menu catalog & pricing

Campaign rules (Lucky Draw 5:1, VIP tiers)

Notification templates (WhatsApp copywriting)

Outcome: satu codebase, tetapi setiap peniaga nampak seperti ‚Äúapp sendiri‚Äù.

2) Multi-Tenant Model (Non-Negotiable)

Anda perlu pilih satu model tenancy:

Option 1 ‚Äî Single Supabase project, row-level multi-tenancy (recommended)

Semua merchant share DB, tetapi setiap row ada merchant_id

Enforce security dengan Supabase RLS (Row Level Security)

Kos rendah, onboarding laju, ops simple

Option 2 ‚Äî Dedicated project per merchant (enterprise)

Lebih secure isolation, tetapi heavy ops + cost

Untuk ‚Äúsemua peniaga boleh guna‚Äù, Option 1 adalah jalan paling pragmatic.

3) Roles & Access Control (Platform Governance)

Minimum RBAC:

customer (public)

staff (operate queue)

manager (products, pricing, campaign)

owner (billing, payouts, settings)

platform_admin (support & compliance)

Rule of thumb: semua query/insert mesti scoped by merchant_id.

4) Onboarding Flow (Merchant Activation Funnel)
Merchant onboarding (B2B)

Sign up ‚Üí create merchant

Setup kiosk profile (name, location, timezone)

Setup menu (products, add-ons, pricing)

Configure campaign (Lucky Draw rules) optional

Configure WhatsApp templates + phone sender (optional)

Generate QR codes:

Customer QR: /m/{slug}/c/splash

Kiosk QR: /m/{slug}/k/display

Selfie QR: /m/{slug}/c/selfie

Customer flow (B2C)

Customer lands at merchant-scoped routes and never sees other merchants.

5) Data Model (Platform-ready)

Every table gets merchant_id:

merchants

merchant_locations (kiosk/site)

products, product_variants, modifiers

orders, order_items

queue_status

campaigns, campaign_rules

lucky_draw_entries (campaign-scoped)

staff_users, roles

media_uploads (selfies)

audit_logs (ops traceability)

This makes reporting and compliance manageable.

6) Payments & Notifications (Scale-Safe Design)
Payments

Two-track strategy:

MVP: ‚ÄúCounter pay‚Äù + manual reconciliation

Scale: Stripe Connect / local aggregator (payout to merchant)

If you aim ‚Äúall merchants‚Äù, you should design for merchant-level payment configuration:

Each merchant can enable/disable payment methods

Platform can take a fee / subscription

WhatsApp

You cannot hardcode one WhatsApp sender for all merchants at scale unless you act as a BSP with shared sender rules.
Pragmatic rollout:

MVP: platform sender number (central)

Scale: merchant connects their own WhatsApp Business API provider credentials

7) ‚ÄúSingle App‚Äù Still Works‚ÄîWith Merchant Routing

You can keep one app but add a merchant namespace:

Landing: /

Marketplace directory optional: /discover

Merchant entry: /m/:slug (merchant landing)

Customer: /m/:slug/c/*

Kiosk: /m/:slug/k/*

Staff: /m/:slug/s/*

Admin: /m/:slug/a/*

This gives you platform + per-merchant funnels without duplicating deployments.

8) Codex Prompt (platform-ize your app, step 1)

Copy-paste into Codex:

Use the sequentialthinking tool.

Objective: Convert the existing single-brand app into a multi-tenant platform where many merchants can use it safely.

Phase 1 Deliverables:
1) Introduce merchant routing namespace:
   - Add routes under /m/:slug/(c|k|s|a)/*
   - Keep "/" as platform landing, and /m/:slug as merchant landing.
2) Add merchant context loader:
   - Resolve :slug -> merchant record from Supabase
   - Provide MerchantProvider with merchant_id, name, theme tokens
3) Update data writes/reads to be merchant-scoped:
   - orders, order_items, queue_status, lucky_draw_entries must include merchant_id
4) Add RLS-compatible structure:
   - Ensure all client queries filter by merchant_id
   - Prepare for Supabase RLS policies (document required policies in RLS.md)
5) Implement a basic merchant admin setup screen:
   - /m/:slug/a/setup
   - configure menu items + campaign settings (simple form)

Constraints:
- Do not break existing flows; provide a default merchant fallback for local dev.
- Keep code modular and typed.
Outputs:
- Updated router + MerchantProvider
- RLS.md draft (policies outline)
- Minimal merchant landing page

9) Commercial Packaging (so it‚Äôs viable as a business)

Typical packaging that converts:

Free: basic POS + queue (limit orders/day)

Pro: WhatsApp notifications + analytics + campaigns (Lucky Draw)

Business: payments + multi-location + staff roles

Enterprise: dedicated tenant + SLA + integrations

This aligns with your KPI goals (data capture + viral loop) and creates upsell levers.

The key decision you must lock now

Untuk multi-merchant, anda nak platform ni:

Abang Colek branded tetapi boleh ‚Äúadd merchant‚Äù (white-label lite)
atau

Neutral platform brand (contoh ‚ÄúKioskOS‚Äù), dan Abang Colek hanya salah satu tenant.

Jika anda jawab 1 atau 2, saya akan bagi:

struktur routes final,

schema + RLS policy set,

onboarding UX flow,

dan prompt Codex untuk implement Phase 1‚Äì2 tanpa scope creep.

PROJEK NIE AKU NAMAKAN NIAGAHUB

