Understood. That report indicates your Lane 2 (in-place rebuild inside abang-colek-brand-os with /legacy) is already working end-to-end: multi-tenant routing, preserved V1, plus added global providers (AI Agent, Tutorial, i18n).

That is a meaningful milestone. However, there are two critical governance issues and one strategic alignment issue we must resolve immediately to keep NIAGAHUB ‚Äúplatform-grade‚Äù and consistent with the locked foundation.

1) Critical security issue: you exposed a live Gemini API key

You pasted:

VITE_GEMINI_API_KEY=AIza...

That is now compromised by definition.

Immediate remediation (non-negotiable)

Revoke / rotate the Gemini API key in Google Cloud console.

Ensure it is never committed and never shared again.

Treat any VITE_* key as client-exposed. If you truly need private calls, move to server-side later. For now, ok for prototype, but it is not secure.

PowerShell checks (run now)

From repo root:

# confirm key is not tracked
git grep -n "VITE_GEMINI_API_KEY"
git grep -n "AIza" .

# ensure env is ignored
type .gitignore


If .env is not ignored, add it immediately:

notepad .gitignore


Add:

.env
.env.*


If .env was committed by accident:

git rm --cached .env
git commit -m "security: remove committed env file"

2) Strategic alignment: this build contradicts the greenfield ‚Äúniagahub-app‚Äù lane

Your locked decision was: NIAGAHUB greenfield, single app, multi-tenant with ABANG-COLEK as first tenant.
What you just built is multi-tenant NIAGAHUB implemented inside ABANG-COLEK Brand OS repo (Lane 2).

This is not ‚Äúwrong,‚Äù but it creates a platform governance risk:

NIAGAHUB platform code is now entangled with a tenant-branded repository

future merchant onboarding becomes harder (branding/logic coupling)

repo name and semantics will confuse contributors and automation

Practical resolution (choose one path and enforce it)

Option A (recommended): treat this as a prototype and extract to niagahub-app/

Keep your V2 structure as reference

Move the V2 app shell into niagahub-app/ (platform repo)

Keep /legacy only inside tenant demo if you want

Option B: formally convert this repo into NIAGAHUB platform repo

Rename repo (or at least set root structure and remove tenant naming)

Move tenant-specific assets to tenants/abang-colek/

Make ‚ÄúBrand OS‚Äù just a tenant theme, not the platform identity

Given your earlier lock, Option A is the cleanest: extract V2 into niagahub-app/ and keep ABANG-COLEK as seeded tenant + theme preset.

3) Architecture governance: your ‚Äúnew features‚Äù must become Tools (not global hardwired)

In your report, these are implemented as ‚Äúglobal providers‚Äù:

AgentProvider (AI Agent)

TutorialProvider (Interactive Tutorial)

LanguageProvider (i18n)

For NIAGAHUB to remain platform-grade and multi-merchant:

Rule

Everything beyond kernel must be Tool-based and merchant-configurable.

So these should become tools like:

tool.ai_assistant (enabled/tier/limits per merchant)

tool.tutorials (onboarding flows per mode)

tool.i18n (enabled languages per merchant)

If you keep them as always-on globals, you‚Äôll eventually get:

performance bloat

merchant complaints (‚ÄúI don‚Äôt want tutorial bubbles‚Äù)

messy monetization

What your report implies is already DONE (good)

Use this as a checklist against our locked foundation:

‚úÖ Strong signals

/m/:slug multi-tenant routing exists

/legacy preserves V1 without interference

Zustand slices match the architecture direction

UI CRT effects exist as reusable layer

Staff/Admin modes exist as separate route namespaces

‚ö†Ô∏è Needs governance hardening

AI key exposure + client-side key model

providers must be controlled by tool registry

ensure merchant isolation is not just ‚ÄúUI routing‚Äù (future: DB/RLS)

Next step: I need one concrete artifact from you to proceed decisively

Since you ran in ANTIGRAVITY/Claude, I cannot see the code. Give me ONE of these:

Option 1 (best): project tree of the new V2 structure

From abang-colek-brand-os root:

tree .\src /f

Option 2: router + providers entrypoint

Paste contents of:

src/main.tsx

src/app/router* (whatever file holds routes)

src/app/providers/* (if exists)

Then I will produce (single-pass, no add-on drift)

A ‚ÄúToolization‚Äù refactor plan: convert AI/Tutorial/i18n into registry-controlled tools with merchant toggles

A clean extraction plan into niagahub-app/ (if we stay on greenfield lane)

Codex/ANTIGRAVITY prompt pack that enforces:

tool gating

tenant scoping

zero new routes beyond ROUTES.md

no secrets in client

One more thing: your dev server is on 5174 in the report. That‚Äôs fine, but we should standardize it in DEV.md and not hardcode ports unless required.

Send me the tree src /f output and I‚Äôll lock the next execution block.

