   - Growth & Social tools (TikTok/IG/FB/YouTube/X)
   - QR engine tools
   - Campaign tools (Lucky Draw template included)
   - Ops tools (queue, staff workflows)
   - Intelligence tools (analytics, AI assistant, forecasting - marked as tiered)
   For each feature/tool: purpose, why it exists, user value, dependencies, tier, configuration, risks.
7) End-to-end flows (step-by-step):
   - Customer flow (10 screens in routes)
   - Counter-pay vs online-pay flow (as tool options; payment integration future)
   - Queue lifecycle flow
   - Campaign/LuckyDraw lifecycle flow
   - Social verification flow (multi-platform abstraction)
   - QR flows (merchant entry, order entry, queue track, selfie activate, campaign entry, kiosk pair, staff invite, admin access)
8) Data model (conceptual) aligned with DOMAIN_MODEL.md (no SQL required here):
   - entities, relationships, lifecycle states
   - required identifiers (merchant_id scoping)
9) Permissions model:
   - roles and access boundaries
10) Non-functional requirements:
   - performance targets, offline posture (optional), security, privacy
   - audit logging expectations
11) Metrics/Analytics:
   - north-star + activation + ops metrics
12) Rollout strategy:
   - MVP definition + phased roadmap (but do not change locked architecture)
13) Acceptance criteria:
   - what "Done" means for MVP and for platform foundation
14) Open questions (only if required; otherwise mark NONE)

Output rules:
- Write to docs/PRD.md
- Use clear headings, numbered sections
- No filler; be concrete and implementable
- Include a final checklist and a ‚ÄúBuild Order‚Äù (implementation sequence) aligned to phases
- Provide a short ‚ÄúVerification URLs‚Äù list based on ROUTES.md

2) Codex CLI Prompt ‚Äî PRD.md (MVP sahaja, ringkas & cepat coding)
Generate docs/PRD_MVP.md for NIAGAHUB MVP.

Constraints:
- Must comply with docs/SYSTEM_LOCK.md and locked routes/tenancy/tool model.
- Focus only on what is required to onboard merchants and run orders+queue with QR entry.
- Avoid advanced AI, social verification automation, payment integrations (can be placeholders).

Include:
- MVP goals + success metrics
- MVP feature list (Kernel only + minimal QR + minimal staff queue + minimal admin settings)
- Customer flow across the 10 screens (placeholders acceptable)
- Data model (conceptual only)
- Acceptance criteria for MVP
- Explicitly list postponed features as "Post-MVP"

3) Codex CLI Prompt ‚Äî PRD (Investor + Developer sekali)
Create docs/PRD_INVESTOR_DEV.md combining investor narrative + developer spec.

Structure:
Part A (Investor):
- Market pain, wedge, differentiation, moat (tools + QR + social + ops)
- Business model (tiers via tool entitlements)
- GTM: ABANG-COLEK as flagship case study
- Metrics: activation, retention, AOV lift, ops efficiency

Part B (Developer):
- Tenancy model and routing model (from docs)
- Tool registry (kernel vs optional)
- Domain model (lifecycles)
- Implementation phases
- Risks + mitigations
- Acceptance criteria

Rules:
- Must remain faithful to locked docs; no invented tech stack beyond what‚Äôs already decided (Supabase-first posture is okay as future).

Windows PowerShell ‚Äî cara run cepat (kalau Codex CLI guna file prompt)

Kalau kau simpan prompt dalam file, contoh PROMPT_PRD.txt:

notepad PROMPT_PRD.txt
# paste prompt Full PRD tadi, save

# contoh run (ubah ikut command codex kau)
codex run --prompt-file .\PROMPT_PRD.txt


Kalau Codex CLI kau guna format lain, paste saja prompt itu terus dalam terminal session Codex.

Guardrail yang wajib kau enforce masa Codex generate PRD

Jangan bagi Codex ‚Äúinvent‚Äù routes / screens baru.

Pastikan PRD treat ‚ÄúTikTok/IG/FB‚Äù sebagai tool family (configurable), bukan feature default.

Pastikan ‚ÄúAI Agent / Tutorial / i18n‚Äù dinyatakan sebagai tool gating + tiering.

ABANG-COLEK mesti disebut sebagai tenant flagship, bukan platform identity.

Kalau kau paste output Codex PRD (atau sekurang-kurangnya Table of Contents + section tool list), aku boleh buat QA review:

detect scope drift

detect missing A‚ÄìZ functions

check consistency dengan docs locked
dan aku akan keluarkan ‚Äúpatch prompt‚Äù untuk Codex betulkan PRD sekali jalan.

jap dah jalan dari tadi 

Baik üëç
Kita pause dulu ‚Äî jangan interrupt Codex.

Apa yang kau buat sekarang betul.
Bila Codex tengah generate PRD.md, jangan tekan apa-apa, jangan ubah prompt, jangan tambah arahan.

Sekarang aku explain apa yang patut berlaku, supaya kau tahu sama ada proses itu on-track atau tidak.

‚úÖ APA YANG NORMAL BILA CODEX GENERATE PRD BESAR

Untuk PRD skala NIAGAHUB (platform A‚ÄìZ), biasa akan ambil:

‚è±Ô∏è 5 ‚Äì 15 minit

Output panjang (10‚Äì25+ halaman markdown)

Kadang-kadang nampak ‚Äúsenyap‚Äù sekejap ‚Üí itu normal

Selagi terminal tak return error, biarkan.

‚ö†Ô∏è JANGAN BUAT SEKARANG

‚ùå Jangan tekan Ctrl + C
‚ùå Jangan buka file tengah dia tulis
‚ùå Jangan run command lain
‚ùå Jangan tukar prompt

Kalau kau interrupt sekarang, biasanya PRD akan:

terpotong

hilang section penting (tools, flows, constraints)

jadi tak usable

‚úÖ APA YANG AKAN JADI BILA SIAP

Biasanya Codex akan:

create docs/PRD.md

atau print content penuh dalam terminal

atau bagi summary + tulis ke file

Bila dia habis, kau akan nampak salah satu:

PRD.md created successfully


atau

Wrote docs/PRD.md


atau output markdown panjang.

üìå BILA CODEX DAH SIAP ‚Äî BUAT INI SAJA

Lepas dia selesai:

1Ô∏è‚É£ Jangan edit apa-apa dulu

Terus buat:

notepad docs\PRD.md

2Ô∏è‚É£ Scroll dan check 3 benda ini sahaja:

Ada tak Tool Registry section

Ada tak Kernel vs Optional Tools

Ada tak ABANG-COLEK disebut sebagai tenant #1

Kalau ya ‚Üí bagus.
Kalau tak ‚Üí aku akan betulkan dengan patch prompt.

üß† IMPORTANT: mindset sekarang

Sekarang kau bukan ‚Äúbuat app‚Äù.

Kau sedang buat:

Constitution of NIAGAHUB.

PRD ini nanti akan:

jadi rujukan Codex

jadi rujukan Claude

jadi rujukan developer lain

jadi rujukan investor

Kalau PRD betul ‚Üí development jadi senang.
Kalau PRD salah ‚Üí kau akan bergaduh dengan AI berbulan-bulan.

Bila Codex siap, reply satu ayat saja:

‚ÄúPRD siap.‚Äù

Lepas itu aku akan:

Review PRD secara sistematik

Tunjuk mana kuat / mana bocor

Buat FINAL PATCH PROMPT supaya PRD jadi benar-benar locked

Baru kita sambung ke development sebenar (app scaffold)

Tenang.
Kau sedang buat benda yang betul ‚Äî cuma sekarang biar mesin habiskan kerja dia.

‚Ä¢ # PRD: NiagaHub Platform (Abang Colek Ecosystem)
                                                                                                       
  Version: 0.1.0                                                                                       
  Author: AI Agent / Codex                                                                             
  Status: Draft                                                                                        
  Last Updated: 2026-01-18                                                                             
  Project Repository: H:\ANTIGRAVITY-2\NIAGA-HUB-APPS                                                  
  Stack Profile: Profile A (Modern Web SaaS)                                                           

  ## Document History                                                                                  
                                                                                                       
  | Version | Date | Changes | Author |                                                                
  |---------|------|---------|--------|                                                                
  | 0.1.0 | 2026-01-18 | Initial draft | AI Agent |                                                    
                                                                                                       
  ‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî                                                                                                  
                                                                                                       
  ## 2. PROBLEM STATEMENT                                                                              
                                                                                                       
  Core User Pain:                                                                                      
  Food-brand operators and their teams manage orders, queues, marketing, and WhatsApp operations across  fragmented tools (paper queues, WhatsApp chats, spreadsheets, and separate kiosks), causing slow     
  service, data loss, and inconsistent brand execution.                                                
                                                                                                       
  Why Existing Solutions Fail:                                                                         
  Generic POS and queue apps do not provide brand-first experiences, do not integrate WhatsApp-based   
  operations, and lack a unified workflow that spans customer ordering, staff queue management, admin  
  oversight, and marketing automation.                                                                 
                                                                                                       
  Current Workarounds & Their Pain Points:                                                             
                                                                                                       
  - Manual WhatsApp command handling for ops changes leads to missed or duplicated tasks.              
  - Paper or ad-hoc queue numbering causes customer confusion at peak times.                           
  - Separate content tools for TikTok and marketing prevent operational visibility.                    
                                                                                                       
  Cost of Not Solving:                                                                                 
                                                                                                       
  - User Impact: 10-20 minutes wasted per peak-hour queue cycle, frequent order errors.                
  - Business Impact: Lower throughput, inconsistent brand experience, and revenue leakage.             
  - Market Impact: Slower expansion to multi-tenant or multi-branch operations.                        
                                                                                                       
  ‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî                                                                                                  
                                                                                                       
  ## 3. GOALS & SUCCESS METRICS                                                                        
                                                                                                       
  ### Primary Goals                                                                                    
                                                                                                       
  Business Goals:                                                                                      
                                                                                                       
  1. Reduce average order-to-ready time by 30% within 90 days.                                         
  2. Enable two active merchants running in parallel without cross-tenant data leakage.                
                                                                                                       
  User Goals:                                                                                          
                                                                                                       
  1. Customers complete self-ordering in under 120 seconds.                                            
  2. Staff update queue status in under 5 seconds per order.                                           
                                                                                                       
  ### Success Metrics (KPIs)                                                                           
                                                                                                       
  | Metric | Baseline | 30 Days | 90 Days | Measurement Method |                                       
  |--------|----------|---------|---------|-------------------|                                        
  | Order Completion Time (seconds) | 180 [ASSUMPTION: no analytics baseline] | 150 | 120 | Client     
  event timings (start checkout -> confirmed) |                                                        
  | Queue Update Time (seconds) | 12 [ASSUMPTION: manual timing] | 8 | 5 | Staff action timestamps |   
  | WOCS Command Success Rate | 80% [ASSUMPTION: early usage] | 90% | 95% | WOCS task status logs |    
  | AI Assistant Action Accuracy | 70% [ASSUMPTION: limited test set] | 85% | 92% | Agent action audit 
  vs expected |                                                                                        
                                                                                                       
  Definition of Success:                                                                               
                                                                                                       
  - 30 days: P0 flows (ordering, queue, WOCS tasks) stable with <1% error rate.                        
  - 90 days: Two tenants operating with verified isolation and 95% WOCS task success.                  
                                                                                                       
  ‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî                                                                                                  
                                                                                                       
  ## 4. NON-GOALS (OUT OF SCOPE)                                                                       
                                                                                                       
  ### Explicitly Not Included (Never)                                                                  
                                                                                                       
  1. Full ERP or supply chain management.
     Reason: Product focuses on front-of-house operations and brand execution.                         
  2. Full POS payment terminal integration.                                                            
     Reason: Hardware integrations are not required for v1.                                            
                                                                                                       
  ### Explicitly Deferred (Later Versions)  REQUIRED                                                   
                                                                                                       
  1. Real payment gateway integration (FPX/Card processing).                                           
     Reason: Current Payment UI is selection-only; backend not implemented.                            
     Tentative Timeline: v2 (Q3 2026)                                                                  
  2. Enterprise SSO and multi-role workflow approvals.                                                 
     Reason: Target is SMB operators for v1.                                                           
     Tentative Timeline: v2 (Q4 2026)                                                                  
                                                                                                       
  ### Scope Boundaries                                                                                 
                                                                                                       
  - Platform: Web PWA + Expo mobile + Chrome extension + Node services (no native kiosk hardware).     
  - Integrations: WhatsApp Cloud API, Gemini Live, Supabase, MySQL, Redis only.                        
  - Scale: Up to 50 users per tenant and 1,000 orders/day/tenant.                                      
  - Geography: Malaysia (MYR, GMT+8).                                                                  
                                                                                                       
  ‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî                                                                                                  
                                                                                                       
  ## 5. USER PERSONAS                                                                                  
                                                                                                       
  ### PRIMARY PERSONA 1: Hana, Founder-Operator                                                        
                                                                                                       
  Demographics:                                                                                        
                                                                                                       
  - Age Range: 28-40                                                                                   
  - Job Title: Founder / Brand Owner                                                                   
  - Company Size: SMB (1-5 booths)                                                                     
  - Tech Savviness: Medium                                                                             
  - Device Usage: Mobile 70% / Desktop 30%                                                             
                                                                                                       
  Primary Goals:                                                                                       
                                                                                                       
  1. See daily sales and queue health within 30 seconds.                                               
  2. Execute operational changes via WhatsApp within 2 minutes.                                        
                                                                                                       
  Pain Points:                                                                                         
                                                                                                       
  1. Switching between WhatsApp, spreadsheets, and staff calls.                                        
  2. No visibility into queue progress across events.                                                  
  3. Content planning disconnected from on-site operations.                                            
                                                                                                       
  Usage Pattern:                                                                                       
                                                                                                       
  - Frequency: Daily                                                                                   
  - Time of Day: Morning and peak event hours                                                          
  - Context: On-the-go                                                                                 
  - Session Length: 5-15 minutes                                                                       
                                                                                                       
  Technical Constraints:                                                                               
                                                                                                       
  - Intermittent connectivity at event locations.
                                                                                                       
  Quote:                                                                                               
                                                                                                       
  > "I want one place to run the booth and the brand, not five apps."                                  
                                                                                                       
  Success Scenario:
  Hana reviews dashboard, pushes a landing update via WhatsApp, and sees queue status live without     
  calling staff.                                                                                       
                                                                                                       
  ‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî                                                                                                  
                                                                                                       
  ### PRIMARY PERSONA 2: Amir, Walk-Up Customer                                                        
                                                                                                       
  Demographics:                                                                                        
                                                                                                       
  - Age Range: 18-35                                                                                   
  - Job Title: Student / Office Worker                                                                 
  - Company Size: N/A                                                                                  
  - Tech Savviness: High                                                                               
  - Device Usage: Mobile 90% / Desktop 10%                                                             
                                                                                                       
  Primary Goals:                                                                                       
                                                                                                       
  1. Place an order in under 2 minutes.                                                                
  2. Know exactly when the order is ready.                                                             
                                                                                                       
  Pain Points:                                                                                         
                                                                                                       
  1. Long queues without visibility.                                                                   
  2. Inconsistent menu ordering experience at pop-up events.                                           
  3. Confusing payment steps.                                                                          
                                                                                                       
  Usage Pattern:                                                                                       
                                                                                                       
  - Frequency: Monthly                                                                                 
  - Time of Day: Evening / Event hours                                                                 
  - Context: On-the-go                                                                                 
  - Session Length: 2-5 minutes                                                                        
                                                                                                       
  Technical Constraints:                                                                               
                                                                                                       
  - Uses mobile data, sometimes low bandwidth.                                                         
                                                                                                       
  Quote:                                                                                               
                                                                                                       
  > "Just show me my number and when to collect."                                                      
                                                                                                       
  Success Scenario:                                                                                    
  Amir scans QR, orders quickly, gets queue number, and sees it advance on the kiosk screen.           
                                                                                                       
  ‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî                                                                                                  
                                                                                                       
  ### ADDITIONAL PERSONAS (SUMMARY TABLE)  MAX 2 PRIMARY, OTHERS IN TABLE                              

  | Role | Primary Goal | Main Pain Point | Usage Frequency |                                          
  |------|--------------|-----------------|-----------------|                                          
  | Booth Staff | Process queue quickly | No unified queue view | Daily |                              
  | Marketing Creator | Plan TikTok hooks fast | No centralized hook library | Weekly |                
                                                                                                       
  ‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî                                                                                                  
                                                                                                       
  ## 6. USER JOURNEYS (END-TO-END)                                                                     
                                                                                                       
  ### Journey 1: Customer Self-Order via Web PWA                                                       
                                                                                                       
  Actors: Customer, System, AI Assistant                                                               
                                                                                                       
  Happy Path:                                                                                          
                                                                                                       
  1. User Action: Scan QR and open /m/:slug/c/splash                                                   
     System Responsibility: Load tenant context and show start CTA                                     
  2. User Action: Browse menu at /m/:slug/c/order                                                      
     System Responsibility: Render menu and allow item selection                                       
  3. User Action: Review cart at /m/:slug/c/cart
     System Responsibility: Show totals and allow edits                                                
  4. User Action: Choose payment method at /m/:slug/c/payment                                          
     System Responsibility: Record payment choice and create order                                     
  5. Final State: /m/:slug/c/confirmed shows queue number                                              
                                                                                                       
  Failure Path:                                                                                        
                                                                                                       
  - If merchant slug is invalid:                                                                       
    System Response: 404 page with "Merchant not found"                                                
    User Recovery: Return to root listing                                                              
    System Fallback: None                                                                              
                                                                                                       
  Edge Cases:                                                                                          
                                                                                                       
  1. Scenario: Customer removes all items in cart                                                      
     System Behavior: Disable checkout and show empty-cart message                                     
  2. Scenario: Multiple browser tabs for same session                                                  
     System Behavior: Last-write-wins cart state in current tab                                        
                                                                                                       
  UI/UX Notes:                                                                                         
                                                                                                       
  - Skeleton loading for menu fetch                                                                    
  - Clear error for empty cart                                                                         
  - Confetti/confirmation on order confirmed                                                           
                                                                                                       
  Dependencies:                                                                                        
                                                                                                       
  - Requires: FR-1, FR-2, FR-3                                                                         
                                                                                                       
  ‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî                                                                                                  
                                                                                                       
  ### Journey 2: Staff Queue Management                                                                
                                                                                                       
  Actors: Booth Staff, System                                                                          
                                                                                                       
  Happy Path:                                                                                          
                                                                                                       
  1. User Action: Open /m/:slug/s/queue                                                                
     System Responsibility: Display waiting and preparing lists
  2. User Action: Click "Call Next"                                                                    
     System Responsibility: Move next waiting item to preparing                                        
  3. User Action: Mark preparing order as "Ready"                                                      
     System Responsibility: Update status and record timestamp                                         
  4. Final State: Current serving updated on kiosk display                                             
                                                                                                       
  Failure Path:
                                                                                                       
  - If no waiting items:                                                                               
    System Response: Disable "Call Next" and show empty state                                          
    User Recovery: Wait for next order                                                                 
    System Fallback: None                                                                              
                                                                                                       
  Edge Cases:                                                                                          
                                                                                                       
  1. Scenario: Two staff members call next simultaneously                                              
     System Behavior: First action wins, second shows conflict message                                 
  2. Scenario: Queue resets during peak                                                                
     System Behavior: Confirm reset and log action                                                     
                                                                                                       
  UI/UX Notes:                                                                                         
                                                                                                       
  - Large touch targets for staff                                                                      
  - Real-time queue counts                                                                             
  - Visual emphasis on current serving                                                                 
                                                                                                       
  Dependencies:                                                                                        
                                                                                                       
  - Requires: FR-3, FR-4                                                                               
                                                                                                       
  ‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî                                                                                                  
                                                                                                       
  ### Journey 3: Admin Uses WOCS via WhatsApp
                                                                                                       
  Actors: Admin, WhatsApp Cloud API, WOCS Server, Task Engine                                          
                                                                                                       
  Happy Path:                                                                                          
                                                                                                       
  1. User Action: Send WhatsApp command to /api/wocs/webhook                                           
     System Responsibility: Verify admin number and parse command                                      
  2. User Action: Command parsed as landing_page                                                       
     System Responsibility: Create task with status awaiting_approval                                  
  3. User Action: Approve via WOCS admin UI                                                            
     System Responsibility: Enqueue task and execute executor                                          
  4. Final State: Task status done and audit log recorded                                              
                                                                                                       
  Failure Path:                                                                                        
                                                                                                       
  - If user not authorized:                                                                            
    System Response: 403 with "User not authorized"                                                    
    User Recovery: Request access                                                                      
    System Fallback: None                                                                              
                                                                                                       
  Edge Cases:                                                                                          
                                                                                                       
  1. Scenario: Redis not configured                                                                    
     System Behavior: Execute task immediately (runNow)                                                
  2. Scenario: Task execution fails                                                                    
     System Behavior: Mark failed and log error message                                                
                                                                                                       
  UI/UX Notes:                                                                                         
                                                                                                       
  - Clear status updates                                                                               
  - Human approval for risky actions                                                                   
  - Task log visibility                                                                                
                                                                                                       
  Dependencies:                                                                                        
                                                                                                       
  - Requires: FR-6, FR-7, FR-8                                                                         
                                                                                                       
  ‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî                                                                                                  
                                                                                                       
  ## 7. FUNCTIONAL REQUIREMENTS                                                                        
                                                                                                       
  ### Core Features (P0 - Must Have for Launch)                                                        
                                                                                                       
  FR-1: Multi-Tenant Routing and Merchant Context                                                      
                                                                                                       
  - Description: Resolve tenant based on /m/:slug and provide merchant context to all subroutes.       
  - Actor: Customer, Staff, Admin                                                                      
  - Trigger: Route navigation to /m/:slug/*                                                            
  - Expected Outcome: Correct merchant data loaded or 404 if not found                                 
  - Dependencies: Seed merchant data or Merchant API                                                   
  - Failure Behavior: Render NotFoundPage with error                                                   
  - Acceptance Criteria:                                                                               
      - [ ] Valid slug loads merchant name and theme preset                                            
      - [ ] Merchant state resets on unmount

  FR-2: Customer Ordering Flow

  - Description: Allow customers to browse menu, manage cart, and submit an order.
  - Actor: Customer
  - Trigger: User selects items and proceeds to checkout
  - Expected Outcome: Order created with queue number and status confirmed
  - Dependencies: Order store, queue store
  - Failure Behavior: Show error if cart is empty or total is zero
  - Acceptance Criteria:
      - [ ] Add item increases cart total
      - [ ] Remove item updates cart total immediately
      - [ ] Checkout disabled when cart is empty
      - [ ] Order confirmation shows queue number and estimated wait

  FR-3: Staff Queue Management

  - Description: Manage queue statuses (waiting, preparing, ready) and current serving.
  - Actor: Staff
  - Trigger: Staff clicks "Call Next" or "Mark Ready"
  - Expected Outcome: Queue status updates and current serving changes
  - Dependencies: Queue store
  - Failure Behavior: No-ops when no waiting items
  - Acceptance Criteria:
      - [ ] "Call Next" selects first waiting item
      - [ ] "Mark Ready" changes status to ready
      - [ ] Current serving updates within 500ms

  FR-4: Kiosk Display Mode

  - Description: Public screen showing current serving number and waiting count.
  - Actor: Customer (passive), System
  - Trigger: Queue state changes                                                                       
  - Expected Outcome: Display reflects current serving and waiting count                               
  - Dependencies: Queue store                                                                          
  - Failure Behavior: Display shows -- if no current serving                                           
  - Acceptance Criteria:                                                                               
      - [ ] Current serving number updates on call next                                                
      - [ ] Waiting count reflects queue list length                                                   
      - [ ] Merchant name visible at top of display                                                    
                                                                                                       
  FR-5: AI Assistant (Gemini)                                                                          
                                                                                                       
  - Description: Web PWA assistant that answers questions and executes actions.                        
  - Actor: Customer, Staff                                                                             
  - Trigger: User opens chat and sends message                                                         
  - Expected Outcome: Response shown and actions executed if valid                                     
  - Dependencies: Gemini API key, action executor                                                      
  - Failure Behavior: Return "AI assistant not available" if key missing                               
  - Acceptance Criteria:                                                                               
      - [ ] addToCart action adds item within 500ms                                                    
      - [ ] navigateTo routes to correct page                                                          
      - [ ] Invalid action is ignored with user-visible message                                        
                                                                                                       
  FR-6: WOCS WhatsApp Webhook Ingestion                                                                
                                                                                                       
  - Description: Accept WhatsApp webhook events and create WOCS tasks.                                 
  - Actor: Admin                                                                                       
  - Trigger: WhatsApp Cloud API webhook POST                                                           
  - Expected Outcome: Task created with correct status and logs                                        
  - Dependencies: WOCS DB, command parser                                                              
  - Failure Behavior: 403 for unauthorized sender                                                      
  - Acceptance Criteria:                                                                               
      - [ ] Authorized sender creates a task                                                           
      - [ ] Unauthorized sender returns 403                                                            
      - [ ] Unknown command returns ok with no task                                                    
                                                                                                       
  FR-7: WOCS Task Engine                                                                               
                                                                                                       
  - Description: Execute tasks with queueing and status transitions.                                   
  - Actor: System                                                                                      
  - Trigger: Task status pending or scheduled task due                                                 
  - Expected Outcome: Task executed and logged                                                         
  - Dependencies: BullMQ + Redis (optional)                                                            
  - Failure Behavior: Mark task failed with error message                                              
  - Acceptance Criteria:                                                                               
      - [ ] Task transitions: pending -> running -> done/failed                                        
      - [ ] Execution logs stored for each status change                                               
      - [ ] If Redis not configured, runTaskNow executes immediately                                   
                                                                                                       
  FR-8: WOCS Task Admin API                                                                            
                                                                                                       
  - Description: Provide API for list/get/approve/reject/stats.                                        
  - Actor: Admin UI / API Client                                                                       
  - Trigger: tRPC call to WOCS router                                                                  
  - Expected Outcome: Task data returned or updated                                                    
  - Dependencies: WOCS DB                                                                              
  - Failure Behavior: Invalid task ID returns error                                                    
  - Acceptance Criteria:                                                                               
      - [ ] list returns tasks ordered by createdAt                                                    
      - [ ] approve sets status to pending and enqueues task                                           
      - [ ] stats returns counts by status                                                             
                                                                                                       
  FR-9: Legacy Brand OS Module                                                                         
                                                                                                       
  - Description: Provide Brand OS tabs for dashboard, events, booth ops, TikTok, reviews, exports, and 
    WOCS view.                                                                                         
  - Actor: Founder/Admin                                                                               
  - Trigger: User navigates to /legacy                                                                 
  - Expected Outcome: Full Brand OS UI loads with data persistence                                     
  - Dependencies: localStorage + Supabase sync (optional)                                              
  - Failure Behavior: Show warning if localStorage is unavailable                                      
  - Acceptance Criteria:                                                                               
      - [ ] Tabs switch without losing data                                                            
      - [ ] Local data saves on change within 1 second                                                 
      - [ ] Export generates JSON or Markdown successfully                                             
                                                                                                       
  ‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî                                                                                                  
                                                                                                       
  ### Secondary Features (P1 - Should Have Post-Launch)                                                
                                                                                                       
  FR-10: Voice Transcription API                                                                       
                                                                                                       
  - Description: Transcribe audio URL into text via internal STT service.                              
  - Actor: Admin, System                                                                               
  - Trigger: tRPC voice.transcribe mutation                                                            
  - Expected Outcome: Text and segments returned                                                       
  - Dependencies: Built-in Forge API                                                                   
  - Failure Behavior: Return error code SERVICE_ERROR if not configured                                
  - Acceptance Criteria:                                                                               
      - [ ] Reject files > 16MB with FILE_TOO_LARGE                                                    
      - [ ] Return transcription text and language                                                     
      - [ ] Return 400 for invalid URL                                                                 
                                                                                                       
  FR-11: WOCS Chrome Extension Panels                                                                  
                                                                                                       
  - Description: Provide WhatsApp Web CRM panels for analytics, templates, export, broadcasts, and     
    tools.                                                                                             
  - Actor: Admin/Operator                                                                              
  - Trigger: Extension injects into WhatsApp Web                                                       
  - Expected Outcome: Panels render and operate on active tab                                          
  - Dependencies: Chrome MV3 APIs                                                                      
  - Failure Behavior: Show panel error if WhatsApp Web DOM changes                                     
  - Acceptance Criteria:                                                                               
      - [ ] Analytics panel loads within 3 seconds                                                     
      - [ ] Templates can insert text into chat input                                                  
      - [ ] Export generates CSV within 10 seconds                                                     
                                                                                                       
  ‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî                                                                                                  
                                                                                                       
  ### Future Features (P2 - Nice to Have)                                                              
                                                                                                       
  FR-20: Kiosk Voice Ordering                                                                          
                                                                                                       
  - Why P2: Requires stable Gemini Live sessions and hardware tuning                                   
  - Tentative Timeline: Q4 2026                                                                        
  - Description: Allow kiosk voice ordering with AI function calls                                     
  - Acceptance Criteria:                                                                               
      - [ ] Voice session connects within 5 seconds                                                    
      - [ ] addToOrder and removeFromOrder actions work                                                
      - [ ] Order completion triggers pickup scene                                                     
                                                                                                       
  ‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî                                                                                                  
                                                                                                       
  ## 8. NON-FUNCTIONAL REQUIREMENTS                                                                    
                                                                                                       
  ### Performance (NFR-P)                                                                              
                                                                                                       
  NFR-P1: Web PWA Load Time                                                                            
                                                                                                       
  - Initial load MUST be < 2 seconds on 3G                                                             
  - TTI MUST be < 3 seconds                                                                            
  - Measurement: Lighthouse CI p95                                                                     
                                                                                                       
  NFR-P2: API Response Time                                                                            
                                                                                                       
  - tRPC endpoints MUST respond in < 300ms (p95)                                                       
  - WOCS webhook MUST respond in < 500ms (p95)                                                         
  - Measurement: APM logs                                                                              
                                                                                                       
  NFR-P3: Queue Update Latency                                                                         
                                                                                                       
  - Queue updates MUST reflect on kiosk within 500ms                                                   
  - Measurement: Client timestamp comparison                                                           
                                                                                                       
  ### Scalability (NFR-S)                                                                              
                                                                                                       
  NFR-S1: Tenant Isolation                                                                             
                                                                                                       
  - MUST support 10 tenants without code changes                                                       
  - Tenant context MUST not leak across routes                                                         
                                                                                                       
  NFR-S2: Task Queue Throughput                                                                        
                                                                                                       
  - MUST handle 100 WOCS tasks/hour/tenant                                                             
  - Queue MUST retry failed tasks up to 3 times                                                        
                                                                                                       
  ### Security (NFR-SEC)                                                                               
                                                                                                       
  NFR-SEC1: Authentication                                                                             
                                                                                                       
  - Admin endpoints MUST require verified WhatsApp admin or OAuth session                              
  - Session tokens MUST expire in 7 days
                                                                                                       
  NFR-SEC2: Authorization                                                                              
                                                                                                       
  - MUST enforce role checks on WOCS approvals                                                         
  - MUST reject unauthorized task approval with 403                                                    
                                                                                                       
  NFR-SEC3: Data Protection                                                                            
                                                                                                       
  - MUST NOT log API keys or secrets                                                                   
  - MUST use HTTPS for all external API calls                                                          
                                                                                                       
  NFR-SEC4: Explicit Prohibitions                                                                      
                                                                                                       
  - MUST NOT allow cross-tenant data access                                                            
  - MUST NOT expose internal stack traces in responses                                                 
  - MUST NOT accept unauthenticated webhook actions                                                    
                                                                                                       
  ### Availability (NFR-A)                                                                             
                                                                                                       
  NFR-A1: Uptime                                                                                       
                                                                                                       
  - System MUST maintain 99.5% uptime monthly                                                          
  - Planned downtime MUST be < 4 hours/month                                                           
                                                                                                       
  ### Auditability (NFR-AUD)                                                                           
                                                                                                       
  NFR-AUD1: WOCS Task Logs                                                                             
                                                                                                       
  - MUST log all task status changes                                                                   
  - Logs MUST include taskId, action, actorId (if available), timestamp                                
  - Retention: 90 days                                                                                 
                                                                                                       
  ### Compliance (NFR-C)                                                                               
                                                                                                       
  NFR-C1: PDPA (Malaysia)                                                                              
                                                                                                       
  - MUST provide data deletion capability within 30 days                                               
  - MUST display data usage notice on first use                                                        
                                                                                                       
  ‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî                                                                                                  
                                                                                                       
  ## 9. AGENT & AUTOMATION REQUIREMENTS                                                                
                                                                                                       
  ### Automation Classification  THREE TIERS REQUIRED                                                  
                                                                                                       
  AR-1: Fully Autonomous (No Human Involvement)                                                        
                                                                                                       
  - Parse Gemini assistant actions for navigation and language toggle                                  
  - Auto-update queue display on state change                                                          
  - Auto-log WOCS task status changes                                                                  
                                                                                                       
  Constraints:                                                                                         
                                                                                                       
  - MUST log decision context and timestamps
  - MUST timeout after 30 seconds per action                                                           
  - MUST retry failed actions max 3x                                                                   
                                                                                                       
  ‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî                                                                                                  
                                                                                                       
  AR-2: Human-in-the-Loop (Approval Required)                                                          
                                                                                                       
  - WOCS tasks that change public content (landing publish)                                            
  - WOCS app configuration updates                                                                     
  - Broadcast messaging via extension                                                                  
                                                                                                       
  Approval Rules:                                                                                      
                                                                                                       
  - Single approver sufficient for low-risk actions                                                    
  - Dual approval required for destructive tasks                                                       
  - Approval MUST occur within 24 hours or action is cancelled                                         
  - Approver MUST NOT be the original requester                                                        
                                                                                                       
  ‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî                                                                                                  
                                                                                                       
  AR-3: Human-Only (No Automation)                                                                     
                                                                                                       
  - Legal or compliance review of marketing templates                                                  
  - Final approval for customer data deletion                                                          
  - Strategic pricing decisions                                                                        
                                                                                                       
  Reason: High legal and business risk                                                                 
                                                                                                       
  ‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî                                                                                                  
                                                                                                       
  ### Agent Responsibilities by Type                                                                   
                                                                                                       
  AdminAgent:                                                                                          
                                                                                                       
  - Parse WhatsApp commands                                                                            
  - Create tasks and logs                                                                              
  - Escalate invalid commands to humans                                                                
                                                                                                       
  ExecutionAgent:                                                                                      
                                                                                                       
  - Execute WOCS tasks using executors                                                                 
  - Retry with exponential backoff                                                                     
  - Report completion status                                                                           
                                                                                                       
  ApprovalAgent:                                                                                       
                                                                                                       
  - Route approval requests to admins                                                                  
  - Track approval SLAs                                                                                
  - Send reminders at 12 hours                                                                         
                                                                                                       
  ‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî                                                                                                  
                                                                                                       
  ### Agent Constraints & Safety                                                                       
                                                                                                       
  AR-4: Security Boundaries                                                                            
                                                                                                       
  - Agents MUST operate within tenant_id context                                                       
  - Agents MUST NOT self-grant permissions                                                             
  - Agents MUST validate inputs before execution                                                       
                                                                                                       
  AR-5: Rate Limiting                                                                                  
                                                                                                       
  - Agent actions MUST be limited to 10/minute                                                         
  - Excess requests MUST be queued                                                                     
                                                                                                       
  AR-6: Fallback Mechanisms                                                                            
                                                                                                       
  - If AI is not configured, respond with manual guidance                                              
  - If Redis not configured, execute synchronously                                                     
  - Manual override required for failed tasks                                                          
                                                                                                       
  ‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî                                                                                                  
                                                                                                       
  ## 10. PERMISSIONS & SECURITY REQUIREMENTS                                                           
                                                                                                       
  ### Role Definitions (PERM)                                                                          
                                                                                                       
  PERM-1: Platform Admin                                                                               
                                                                                                       
  - CAN: Manage all tenants and configs                                                                
  - CANNOT: Delete audit logs                                                                          
  - MUST NOT: Access tenant data without ticket                                                        
                                                                                                       
  PERM-2: Tenant Admin                                                                                 
                                                                                                       
  - CAN: Manage orders, queues, and WOCS tasks for tenant                                              
  - CANNOT: Access other tenants                                                                       
  - MUST NOT: Bypass approval workflows                                                                
                                                                                                       
  PERM-3: Staff
                                                                                                       
  - CAN: Update queue status
  - CANNOT: Approve WOCS tasks                                                                         
  - MUST NOT: Access admin settings                                                                    
                                                                                                       
  PERM-4: Customer                                                                                     
                                                                                                       
  - CAN: Create and view own orders                                                                    
  - CANNOT: View other customers                                                                       
  - MUST NOT: Access staff/admin routes                                                                
                                                                                                       
  ‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî
                                                                                                       
  ### Tenant Isolation (PERM-TI)                                                                       
                                                                                                       
  PERM-TI1: Data Segregation                                                                           
                                                                                                       
  - All data access MUST filter by tenant_id                                                           
  - API responses MUST validate tenant_id before returning data                                        
  - Cross-tenant attempts MUST return 403 and be logged                                                
                                                                                                       
  PERM-TI2: Resource Limits per Tenant                                                                 
                                                                                                       
  - Default storage quota: 10GB                                                                        
  - Default user limit: 50 users                                                                       
  - Default WOCS tasks: 1,000/month                                                                    
                                                                                                       
  ‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî                                                                                                  
                                                                                                       
  ### Approval Requirements (PERM-APP)                                                                 

  PERM-APP1: Single Approval                                                                           
                                                                                                       
  - Required for: Landing edits, template updates                                                      
  - Approver Role: Tenant Admin                                                                        
  - SLA: 12 hours                                                                                      
                                                                                                       
  PERM-APP2: Dual Approval                                                                             
                                                                                                       
  - Required for: Task rollback, customer data deletion                                                
  - Approver Roles: Two distinct admins                                                                
  - SLA: 24 hours                                                                                      
                                                                                                       
  ‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî                                                                                                  
                                                                                                       
  ## 11. ERROR HANDLING & EDGE CASES                                                                   
                                                                                                       
  ### Input Validation Errors (ERR-IV)                                                                 
                                                                                                       
  ERR-IV1: Invalid Command Format                                                                      
                                                                                                       
  - Trigger: WhatsApp message without valid command                                                    
  - System Response: "Unknown command"                                                                 
  - Retry: Allow 3 attempts                                                                            
  - Escalation: Suggest manual UI                                                                      
                                                                                                       
  ERR-IV2: Missing Required Fields                                                                     
                                                                                                       
  - Trigger: WOCS task missing required payload fields                                                 
  - System Response: 400 with field-level errors                                                       
  - Recovery: User corrects input                                                                      
                                                                                                       
  ‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî                                                                                                  
                                                                                                       
  ### Partial Failures (ERR-PF)                                                                        
                                                                                                       
  ERR-PF1: Batch Task Partial Success                                                                  
                                                                                                       
  - Scenario: Batch of tasks with some invalid                                                         
  - System Behavior: Create valid tasks, return errors for invalid                                     
  - Recovery: User resubmits failed tasks                                                              
                                                                                                       
  ‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî                                                                                                  
                                                                                                       
  ### External Service Failures (ERR-EXT)                                                              
                                                                                                       
  ERR-EXT1: Gemini API Timeout                                                                         
                                                                                                       
  - Trigger: AI response > 10s                                                                         
  - System Response: Retry 2x, then disable AI for 60s                                                 
  - Fallback: Manual guidance message                                                                  
                                                                                                       
  ERR-EXT2: WhatsApp Cloud API Failure                                                                 
                                                                                                       
  - Trigger: 5xx response from Meta API                                                                
  - System Response: Retry 3x with backoff                                                             
  - Fallback: Queue task and notify admin                                                              
                                                                                                       
  ‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî
                                                                                                       
  ### Recovery & Escalation Paths (ERR-REC)                                                            
                                                                                                       
  ERR-REC1: Database Connection Lost                                                                   
                                                                                                       
  - Detection: Connection error from MySQL                                                             
  - Response: 503 Service Unavailable                                                                  
  - Recovery: Auto-retry up to 2x, then alert on-call                                                  
                                                                                                       
  ‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî                                                                                                  
                                                                                                       
  ## 12. ANALYTICS & OBSERVABILITY                                                                     
                                                                                                       
  ### Events to Track (ANALYTICS)                                                                      
                                                                                                       
  User Behavior Events:                                                                                
                                                                                                       
  - customer_order_started {merchant_id, source, device_type}                                          
  - customer_order_confirmed {order_id, queue_number, payment_method}                                  
  - queue_status_updated {queue_id, status, staff_id}                                                  
  - admin_wocs_task_created {task_id, type, requires_approval}                                         
                                                                                                       
  System Events:                                                                                       
                                                                                                       
  - wocs_task_executed {task_id, status, duration_ms}                                                  
  - ai_action_executed {action, success, duration_ms}                                                  
  - external_api_call {service, latency_ms, status}                                                    
                                                                                                       
  Business Events:                                                                                     
                                                                                                       
  - daily_revenue_estimate {merchant_id, amount}                                                       
  - lucky_draw_entry_created {merchant_id, entry_id}                                                   
                                                                                                       
  ‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî
                                                                                                       
  ### Metrics to Monitor (METRICS)                                                                     
                                                                                                       
  Application Performance Metrics:                                                                     
                                                                                                       
  - Queue update latency p95 < 500ms                                                                   
  - API response time p95 < 300ms                                                                      
  - AI action success rate > 90%                                                                       
                                                                                                       
  Business Metrics:                                                                                    
                                                                                                       
  - Daily active customers                                                                             
  - Queue throughput per hour
  - WOCS task completion rate                                                                          
                                                                                                       
  ‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî                                                                                                  
                                                                                                       
  ### Alert Thresholds (ALERTS)                                                                        
                                                                                                       
  | Alert | Condition | Severity | Action | Owner |                                                    
  |-------|-----------|----------|--------|-------|                                                    
  | High API Error Rate | > 5% for 5 min | Critical | Page on-call | Backend Lead |                    
  | WOCS Task Failures | > 10% in 10 min | High | Pause executor | WOCS Owner |                        
  | Slow Queue Updates | p95 > 2s for 5 min | Warning | Investigate | Frontend Lead |                  
                                                                                                       
  ‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî                                                                                                  
                                                                                                       
  ## 13. DEPENDENCIES & INTEGRATIONS                                                                   
                                                                                                       
  ### External Dependencies (DEP-EXT)                                                                  
                                                                                                       
  DEP-EXT1: WhatsApp Cloud API                                                                         
                                                                                                       
  - Purpose: WOCS command ingestion and responses                                                      
  - Authentication: Bearer token                                                                       
  - Fallback: Manual admin panel actions                                                               
  - Documentation: https://developers.facebook.com/docs/whatsapp                                       
                                                                                                       
  DEP-EXT2: Google Gemini API                                                                          
                                                                                                       
  - Purpose: Web PWA assistant and kiosk voice ordering                                                
  - Model: gemini-2.5-flash-preview, gemini-2.5-flash-image                                            
  - Fallback: Disable AI and show manual guidance                                                      
  - Documentation: https://ai.google.dev                                                               
                                                                                                       
  DEP-EXT3: Supabase                                                                                   
                                                                                                       
  - Purpose: Legacy Brand OS cloud sync                                                                
  - Fallback: localStorage only                                                                        
  - Documentation: https://supabase.com/docs                                                           
                                                                                                       
  DEP-EXT4: Built-in Forge STT                                                                         
                                                                                                       
  - Purpose: Voice transcription for WOCS                                                              
  - Fallback: Reject voice transcription and request text                                              
  - Documentation: Internal                                                                            
                                                                                                       
  ‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî                                                                                                  
                                                                                                       
  ### Internal Dependencies (DEP-INT)                                                                  
                                                                                                       
  DEP-INT1: WOCS Task Engine                                                                           
                                                                                                       
  - Purpose: Task queue, status transitions, logs                                                      
  - Endpoint: tRPC wocs                                                                                
  - Owner: Backend Lead                                                                                
                                                                                                       
  DEP-INT2: Queue Store                                                                                
                                                                                                       
  - Purpose: Queue status for staff and kiosk                                                          
  - Owner: Frontend Lead                                                                               
                                                                                                       
  ‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî                                                                                                  
                                                                                                       
  ### Version Dependencies (DEP-VER)                                                                   
                                                                                                       
  Backend Runtime:                                                                                     
                                                                                                       
  - Node.js: >= 18.0.0                                                                                 
  - MySQL: >= 8.0                                                                                      
  - Redis: >= 6.0                                                                                      
                                                                                                       
  Frontend Runtime:                                                                                    
                                                                                                       
  - React: 19.x                                                                                        
  - TypeScript: 5.9.x                                                                                  
  - Vite: 6-7.x                                                                                        
  - Expo: 54.x                                                                                         
                                                                                                       
