  ## 14. RISKS & MITIGATIONS                                                                           
                                                                                                       
  | Risk ID | Description | Impact | Probability | Owner | Mitigation Strategy |                       
  |---------|-------------|--------|-------------|-------|---------------------|                       
  | RISK-1 | Client-side API key exposure (Gemini/Supabase/Wassist) | High | Medium | Security Lead |  
  Move keys to server proxy, apply referrer restrictions |                                             
  | RISK-2 | WOCS tasks lost on server restart (in-memory queue) | High | Medium | Backend Lead |      
  Persist tasks in DB and use Redis queue |                                                            
  | RISK-3 | No auth on admin/staff web routes | High | Medium | Frontend Lead | Add auth guard and    
  session checks |                                                                                     
  | RISK-4 | WhatsApp API outage | Medium | Low | WOCS Owner | Queue tasks and allow manual UI fallback  |                                                                                                    
  | RISK-5 | Tenant data leakage via client-only state | Critical | Low | Engineering Manager |        
  Implement server-side tenant validation |
                                                                                                       
  ### Tech Debt & Gaps (Code Audit)                                                                    
                                                                                                       
  - [SECURITY RISK] Client-side API keys in abang-colek-brand-os/src/lib/supabase.ts and abang-colek-  
    brand-os/src/lib/gemini.ts.                                                                        
  - [SECURITY RISK] Public WOCS REST endpoints in wocs-server/src/index.ts lack auth and rate limiting.  - [SCALABILITY RISK] WOCS queue in wocs-server/src/services/taskQueue.ts is in-memory and non-       
    persistent.                                                                                        
  - [TECH DEBT] wocs-server/src/routes/* not mounted; README lists endpoints not available.            
  - [TECH DEBT] Multi-tenant data is seed-only in abang-colek-brand-os/src/data/seed/merchants.ts.     
                                                                                                       
  ‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî                                                                                                  
                                                                                                       
  ## 15. OPEN QUESTIONS & ASSUMPTIONS                                                                  
                                                                                                       
  ### Open Questions (QUESTIONS)                                                                       
                                                                                                       
  Q1: Should multi-tenant data be stored in Supabase or MySQL for v1?                                  
                                                                                                       
  - Decision Needed By: 2026-02-01                                                                     
  - Blocked: Tenant isolation implementation                                                           
  - Impact if No: Risk of cross-tenant data mixing                                                     
                                                                                                       
  Q2: Which payment gateway will be used for online payments?                                          
                                                                                                       
  - Decision Needed By: 2026-02-15                                                                     
  - Blocked: Payment flow implementation                                                               
  - Impact: Affects backend design and compliance                                                      
                                                                                                       
  Q3: Do we require SSO for tenant admins?                                                             
                                                                                                       
  - Decision Needed By: 2026-03-01                                                                     
  - Blocked: Auth design                                                                               
  - Impact: May extend timeline by 3-4 weeks                                                           
                                                                                                       
  Q4: Target launch date for kiosk voice ordering?                                                     
                                                                                                       
  - Current Assumption: 2026-10-01                                                                     
  - Blocked: Hardware testing timeline                                                                 
  - Impact if Changed: May affect AI budget and kiosk scope                                            
                                                                                                       
  ‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî                                                                                                  
                                                                                                       
  ### Assumptions (ASSUMPTIONS)                                                                        
                                                                                                       
  [ASSUMPTION-1: no production analytics]: Baseline order completion time is 180 seconds.              
                                                                                                       
  - If False  Impact: KPI targets must be recalibrated; performance goals may change by +/- 30 seconds.  - Validation: Instrument checkout events and measure over 7 days.                                    
                                                                                                       
  [ASSUMPTION-2: limited tenant scale]: Each tenant has <= 50 daily active users in v1.                
                                                                                                       
  - If False  Impact: Need stronger caching and paging, +3 weeks.                                      
  - Validation: Pilot tenant usage logs.                                                               
                                                                                                       
  [ASSUMPTION-3: WhatsApp admins are pre-registered]: Admin numbers are provisioned before webhook use.                                                                                                       
  - If False  Impact: Need onboarding workflow and admin verification UI, +2 weeks.                    
  - Validation: Admin onboarding survey.                                                               
                                                                                                       
  [ASSUMPTION-4: Malaysia-only operations]: All transactions in MYR, timezone GMT+8.                   
                                                                                                       
  - If False  Impact: Add multi-currency and timezone support, +4 weeks.                               
  - Validation: Market expansion roadmap review.                                                       
                                                                                                       
  ‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî                                                                                                  
                                                                                                       
  ## 16. ACCEPTANCE CRITERIA                                                                           
                                                                                                       
  ### Product-Level Acceptance (ACCEPT-PROD)                                                           
                                                                                                       
  ACCEPT-PROD-1: End-to-End Customer Order Flow                                                        
  Given a valid merchant slug,                                                                         
  When a customer adds items and checks out,                                                           
  Then a queue number is issued within 10 seconds.                                                     
                                                                                                       
  ACCEPT-PROD-2: Multi-Tenant Isolation                                                                
  Given Tenant A and Tenant B exist,                                                                   
  When Tenant A navigates to Tenant B slug,                                                            
  Then Tenant A sees only Tenant B context and no Tenant A data.                                       
                                                                                                       
  ACCEPT-PROD-3: WOCS Approval Gate                                                                    
  Given a WOCS task requiring approval,                                                                
  When the task is created,                                                                            
  Then it remains awaiting_approval until an admin approves it.                                        
                                                                                                       
  ACCEPT-PROD-4: Queue Update Performance                                                              
  Given staff updates queue status,                                                                    
  When the update is submitted,                                                                        
  Then the kiosk display reflects the change in < 500ms.                                               
                                                                                                       
  ‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî                                                                                                  
                                                                                                       
  ### Feature-Level Acceptance (ACCEPT-FEAT)                                                           
                                                                                                       
  For FR-1: Multi-Tenant Routing                                                                       
                                                                                                       
  - [ ] /m/abang-colek loads Abang Colek merchant data                                                 
  - [ ] /m/demo-merchant loads Demo Merchant data
  - [ ] Invalid slug shows NotFoundPage with error message

  For FR-5: AI Assistant

  - [ ] Chat opens via FAB and closes on toggle
  - [ ] Action JSON in <action> tags executes
  - [ ] Missing API key shows configuration warning

  For FR-7: WOCS Task Engine

  - [ ] Task status transitions recorded in logs
  - [ ] Failed tasks include error message
  - [ ] Scheduled tasks execute when due

  ‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî

  ### Quality Gates for Production (ACCEPT-QA)

  Before Production Deployment, ALL of these MUST be TRUE:

  - [ ] Functional: All P0 FRs implemented and tested
  - [ ] Non-Functional: NFR-P1, NFR-P2, NFR-SEC1 validated
  - [ ] Security: No critical findings open
  - [ ] Monitoring: Alerts configured for API errors and WOCS failures
  - [ ] Documentation: Operator runbook and setup guide completed
  - [ ] Tenant Isolation: Verified by integration tests
  - [ ] Rollback Plan: Documented and tested in staging

