Sekarang jawab satu ayat sahaja üëá

‚ÄúYa, jadikan PRD ini platform-first dan ABANG-COLEK sebagai tenant #1.‚Äù

Lepas itu aku terus bagi
üëâ PROMPT PATCH SIAP COPY‚ÄìPASTE KE ANTIGRAVITY
(Claude Opus 4.5‚Äìoptimized, sekali jalan, final).

‚ÄúYa, jadikan PRD ini platform-first dan ABANG-COLEK sebagai tenant #1.‚Äù

Baik.
Keputusan ini telah di-lock secara strategik.

Sekarang kita masuk mod execution sebenar ‚Äî bukan brainstorm lagi.

Di bawah ini aku beri PROMPT PATCH RASMI yang kau boleh copy‚Äìpaste terus ke ANTIGRAVITY (Claude Opus 4.5).

Prompt ini tidak rewrite PRD dari kosong.
Ia memperbetulkan PRD sedia ada supaya menjadi PLATFORM-FIRST, sambil mengekalkan semua kekuatan teknikal yang Codex sudah hasilkan.

‚úÖ OFFICIAL PRD PATCH PROMPT

(ANTIGRAVITY ¬∑ Claude Opus 4.5)

Gunakan prompt ini 100% ‚Äî jangan ubah ayat.

You are acting as a Senior Principal Product Architect.

Context:
We already have a detailed PRD.md generated for NIAGAHUB, but it is currently written in a brand-centric way (‚ÄúAbang Colek ecosystem‚Äù).

Your task is NOT to rewrite from scratch.

Your task is to PATCH and REFRAME the existing PRD so that:

- NIAGAHUB is a neutral multi-tenant SaaS platform
- ABANG-COLEK is explicitly positioned as:
  ‚Üí Tenant #1
  ‚Üí flagship reference tenant
  ‚Üí NOT the platform identity

This is a platform-first refactor.

‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ
MANDATORY CONSTITUTION (NON-NEGOTIABLE)
‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ

1. NIAGAHUB is a single-app, multi-tenant operating system.
2. All merchants are tenants.
3. ABANG-COLEK is tenant #1 only.
4. No feature may exist without belonging to:
   - Kernel (always-on)
   - or Tool (optional, configurable, tiered)
5. Everything beyond Kernel MUST be a tool.
6. Tenant isolation is absolute (merchant_id everywhere).
7. Brand-specific behaviors must be tenant configurations, never platform assumptions.

‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ
PATCH OBJECTIVES
‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ

Modify the existing PRD.md by applying the following transformations:

A) TITLE & POSITIONING
- Change document title to:
  ‚ÄúPRD: NIAGAHUB Platform (Multi-Tenant Commerce OS)‚Äù
- Add a short upfront section:
  ‚ÄúABANG-COLEK as Reference Tenant #1‚Äù
  explaining:
  - why it exists
  - what it represents
  - what it does NOT control

B) PLATFORM NARRATIVE LAYER
Insert a new early section:
‚ÄúPlatform Philosophy & Structural Model‚Äù

This must clearly explain:
- kernel vs tools
- why modularity exists
- how different merchant types enable different tool sets
- how NIAGAHUB avoids feature bloat via tool registry

C) FEATURE ‚Üí TOOL NORMALIZATION
For every feature currently described as a fixed capability:

Convert it into a TOOL with:
- tool name
- category
- purpose
- when merchants need it
- dependencies
- tier (Core / Growth / Advanced / Enterprise)
- enabled_by_default (true/false)

Mandatory conversions include:
- AI Assistant
- WOCS
- Voice ordering
- Campaigns
- Social integrations
- Chrome extension
- Legacy Brand OS

Legacy Brand OS MUST be reframed as:
‚ÄúReference Implementation Tool (Tenant #1 only)‚Äù
and NOT a platform feature.

D) TOOL REGISTRY SECTION (NEW)
Insert a full Tool Registry table including:

Kernel (Always On):
- Merchant
- Menu
- Order
- Queue
- Roles
- QR Engine (base)

Optional Tools:
- Payments (future)
- AI Assistant
- WOCS Automation
- Campaign Engine
- Social Channel Connectors
- Analytics
- Voice Ordering
- CRM / Customer Insights
- Extension Toolkit

Each tool must clearly state:
- optionality
- configuration surface
- entitlement tier

E) ROUTING & MODES CLARITY
Clarify that:
- customer / staff / kiosk / admin are MODES within one app
- not separate applications
- resolved purely by route + role + tenant context

F) TENANT SAFETY REASSERTION
Add a section:
‚ÄúTenant Safety & Governance Rules‚Äù

Must explicitly state:
- no cross-tenant reads
- no cross-tenant writes
- no shared state
- no shared cache keys
- audit logs are tenant-scoped

G) LANGUAGE NORMALIZATION
Remove or neutralize any phrasing that implies:
- this platform belongs to Abang Colek
- features are only for food brands
- booth-specific assumptions as global defaults

Replace with:
- ‚Äúmerchant‚Äù
- ‚Äútenant‚Äù
- ‚Äúreference tenant example (Abang Colek)‚Äù

‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ
OUTPUT REQUIREMENTS
‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ

- Update the existing PRD.md (do not create a new file).
- Preserve all detailed engineering sections, FRs, NFRs, risks, metrics, and acceptance criteria.
- Do NOT remove complexity ‚Äî only reframe it.
- Add clarity, not abstraction fluff.
- The final PRD must be suitable for:
  - engineers
  - platform onboarding
  - investors
  - future AI agents (Codex, Claude, Gemini)

At the end of the document, add a final section:

‚ÄúPlatform Lock Declaration‚Äù

Stating:
- NIAGAHUB is platform-first
- merchants are tenants
- ABANG-COLEK is tenant #1
- this PRD is the single source of truth
- any future feature must conform to kernel/tool architecture

Do not ask questions.
Do not suggest alternatives.
Execute the patch fully and output the updated PRD.md.

üîí APA YANG AKAN TERJADI LEPAS INI

Selepas Claude Opus 4.5 jalan prompt ini:

‚úÖ PRD kau akan jadi:

platform-clean

